    "updated_at": "2016-03-28T20:23:19Z",
    "body": "Hey, if you're interested in what's going inside Electron, you can find the code [over here](https://github.com/atom/brightray/tree/master/browser) (look for the notification files). The implementations are fairly simple on all three platforms, so if you can't immediately find a feature, it's probably not there - people would probably really like a PR though ;-)\n\nOn Windows, we're not using the latest and greatest Windows 10 notifications, but instead the Windows 8 notification APIs (ensuring that they run well on 8, 8.1, 10). I'm not sure if that's the reason, but that might be why they are not persistent.\n"
